[3] Ebola: Europe-Africa research collaborations
Date: 4 Nov 2015
Source: Lancet Infectious Diseases [edited]
http://www.thelancet.com/journals/laninf/article/PIIS1473-3099(15)00375-8/fulltext

Ebola: Europe-Africa research collaborations
---------------------------------------------------
The Europe-Africa clinical research response to Ebola has been impressive, and includes vaccine safety studies in west Africa(2, 3) the encouraging results of the ring vaccination trial in Guinea coordinated by WHO(4), the first ever drug trial in Ebola undertaken by the favipiravir (JIKI) trial consortium (NCT02329054)(5), the RAPIDE consortium trials of brincidofovir (PACTR201411000939962) and TKM-130803 (PACTR201501000997429), and the Ebola-Tx (NCT02342171) and Ebola-CP (ISRCTN13990511) trials of convalescent plasma... - more
Ref: Horby PW et al. (2015) Ebola: Europe-Africa research collaborations Lancet ID 15(11):1258-1259 (same as source URL)
